The paper deals with a multiagent system and applies concepts from welfare economics and social choice theory to assess social welfare. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Multiagent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses negotiation frameworks, which is a topic covered in Game Theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper uses artificial intelligence techniques to study the negotiation framework, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses how deals affect social welfare, which is a topic covered in Learning (cs.LG) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
